BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (43): BTV-8, DENMARK, OIE
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 15 Oct 2007
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database) weekly
disease information 2007; 20(42) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Bluetongue, Denmark
-------------------
Information received on (and dated) 13 Oct 2007 from Dr Jan Mousing,
Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and
Fisheries, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Fisheries, Soborg,
Denmark

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 11 Oct 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 13 Oct 2007
Report date: 13 Oct 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Oct 2007
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: bluetongue virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: entire country

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (BT2007/1) location: Sakskobing, Storstroms Amt
Date of start of outbreak: 11 Oct 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: sheep
Susceptible: 250
Cases: 1
Deaths: 1
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: a sheep herd with 100 sheep and 150 lambs. Only
one animal showed clinical signs such as fever, respiratory disorder,
salivation, and erosion in the oral cavity. The affected animal died
less than 48 hours after showing clinical signs.

Outbreak statistics
Species: Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate: 0.40 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0.40 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0.40 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: A 20 km (12.4 mi) infection zone and a 150
km (93.2 mi) restriction zone have been established according to EU
legislation.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Institute (national laboratory)
Species: sheep
Test: antibody detection ELISA (enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay)
Test date: 13 Oct 2007
Result: positive

Species: sheep
Test: polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date: 13 Oct 2007
Result: positive

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The location of the outbreak on the island of Lolland in Sjaelland (or
should it be Zealand?), just across from Germany, can be seen at the end
of the OIE report referenced above or
at<http://www.geonames.org/2614328/sakskobing.html>.

Please note the low morbidity and mortality rates in this outbreak. - Mod.PC]

[While the virus serotype is not stated, there is a very high
probability that this is BTV-8 and that forthcoming laboratory
serotyping will confirm this. - Mods.AS/LM]
